                        <provenance type="found">Also known as the 'Maiden Stone' or the 'Drumdurno Stone', the ogham was not discovered until the 2000s and the inscription was first mentioned in <date>2017</date> (Barnes 2017, 2-3). The stone was first recorded in <date>1726</date> (Gordon 1726, 59) and first illustrated in <date>1788</date> (Cordiner 1788, 33). It stands within a small agricultural enclosure by the roadside, near the Chapel of Garioch, just south of the A96 and northwest of Inverurie (Barnes 2017). It has been suggested that the stone was moved from its original location a few yards westwards around <date cert="low">1866</date> to allow for the construction of a road (Barnes 2017, 4).  
                        </provenance>
